---
import BaseLayout from "../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="Prompt template — Harwell Prompt Engineering"
  pageDescription="Use this structure to get consistent, useful answers from AI when writing or reviewing code."
  showSocials={false}
>
  <article class="course-page handout-page">
    <header>
      <p class="course-breadcrumb"><a href="/courses/harwell-ai">Harwell — Prompt Engineering</a></p>
      <h1>Prompt template</h1>
    </header>

    <p>
      Use this structure to get consistent, useful answers from AI when writing or
      reviewing code.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Context (role + environment)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Role:</strong> e.g. "You are a senior Java developer..."</li>
        <li><strong>Stack:</strong> e.g. "Spring Boot 3, Java 17, JUnit 5, Mockito."</li>
        <li><strong>Style:</strong> e.g. "Use constructor injection, no @Autowired. Prefer immutable DTOs."</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Clarity (one clear ask)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>State the <strong>task</strong> in one sentence.</li>
        <li>Specify <strong>input</strong> (e.g. "Here is the method..." or "Given the entity below...").</li>
        <li>Specify <strong>output</strong> (e.g. "Return only the refactored method" or "List the steps, then the code").</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Constraints (what to avoid)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>e.g. "Do not use deprecated APIs."</li>
        <li>e.g. "Do not add dependencies we don't already have."</li>
        <li>e.g. "Keep the same method signature."</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Example (paste into your AI tool)</h2>
      <pre class="handout-pre"><code>Context:
- Role: Senior Java developer
- Stack: Spring Boot 3, Java 17, JUnit 5, Mockito
- Style: Constructor injection, no @Autowired

Task: Generate a JPA repository interface and a service method that returns all books by author. Return ResponseEntity&lt;List&lt;Book&gt;&gt;.

Constraints:
- Use the existing Book entity. Do not add new dependencies.
- Include error handling for empty results.</code></pre>
    </section>

    <p class="handout-footer">
      From the Harwell Prompt Engineering course. Replace placeholders with your own context.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .course-page {
    max-width: 90ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .handout-page .course-breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .handout-page .course-breadcrumb a {
    color: var(--site-green);
  }

  .handout-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.35rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--site-green);
  }

  .handout-page section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .handout-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .handout-pre {
    background: rgba(0, 105, 46, 0.08);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--site-green);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .handout-pre code {
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .handout-footer {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #666;
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
